@baseUrl = https://www.marrs.work
@localUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8000
@newsId = 1
@podcastId = 1
@taskId = REPLACE_WITH_TASK_ID
@openid = test_openid
@entity = OpenAI
@topic = AI
@word = example

### News list used by home page
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/news/list?page=1&page_size=10

### News list by category used when switching categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/news/list?page=1&page_size=10&category=business

### News categories used by home page category selector
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/news/categories

### News detail used by article detail page
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/news/{{newsId}}

### News search used by search box and entity Read Articles action
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/news/search?q=AI&page=1&page_size=10

### News sentiment endpoint exists in backend, not currently called by index page
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/news/{{newsId}}/sentiments

### Dictionary lookup used when tapping a word in article detail
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dict/lookup?word={{word}}


### Dictionary audio proxy used after dictionary lookup returns an audio key
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dict/audio?key={{word}}&type=1

### Podcast list used by podcast page
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/podcast/list?page=1&page_size=10

### Podcast detail used by full podcast player
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/podcast/{{podcastId}}

### Podcast audio proxy exists in backend
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/podcast/{{podcastId}}/audio

### Knowledge graph trending entities used by Graph / Heat Trends topic selector
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge-graph/trending-entities?days=7&limit=10

### Knowledge graph trends used by Heat Trends page
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge-graph/trends?topic={{topic}}

### Knowledge graph entity articles used by entity detail bottom sheet
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge-graph/entity-articles?entity={{entity}}&limit=5

### Knowledge graph entities exists in backend; Entity Network currently uses static demo graph
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge-graph/entities?topic={{topic}}

### Chat question used by article detail AI chat
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/question
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "news_id": {{newsId}},
  "question": "Summarize this article in one sentence.",
  "history": []
}

### Record reading history used after opening a news detail when user is logged in
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/history
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{openid}}",
  "news_id": {{newsId}}
}

### Get reading history used by Me page
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/history?user_id={{openid}}&page=1&page_size=20

### WeChat login used by Me page login flow
### Replace code with a real wx.login code from the mini program.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "REPLACE_WITH_WX_LOGIN_CODE",
  "nickname": "Test User",
  "avatar_url": ""
}

### Admin health exists in backend; useful for deployment smoke test
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/health

### Admin stats exists in backend; useful for backend dashboard smoke test
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/stats

### Admin cleanup exists in backend; run carefully
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/cleanup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "days": 30
}

### AI process exists in backend; not currently called by mini program index page
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batch_size": 10,
  "max_workers": 10
}

### AI task status after /api/ai/process returns a task_id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/ai/status/{{taskId}}

### Crawler trigger exists in backend; run carefully
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/crawler/trigger
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "bbc"
}

### Crawler task status after /api/crawler/trigger returns a task_id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/crawler/status/{{taskId}}
